WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.520 --> 00:00:05.990
- Where we goin'. Mama?
- We goin' to pay tribute to your daddy.

2
00:00:08.160 --> 00:00:10.628
Our house used to be
a whole different thing.

3
00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:12.910
Strangers rested there.

4
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.788
People leavin' messages.
Folks comin' and goin' all the time.

5
00:00:16.920 --> 00:00:20.469
It was a happy house when
I first got there with Denver
strapped to my chest...

6
00:00:20.600 --> 00:00:22.830
waitin' on her daddy to come.

7
00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:24.751
Daddy.

8
00:00:24.840 --> 00:00:27.957
Halle bought Baby Suggs' freedom...

9
00:00:28.040 --> 00:00:30.713
but slavery done already
busted her legs...

10
00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:34.349
and busted her back.
hands. everything.

11
00:00:34.440 --> 00:00:37.352
When she come here. she ain't had
nothin' left to make no livin' with...

12
00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:40.233
besides her heart.

13
00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.998
Baby Suggs used to preach
right here.

14
00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:52.638
Let the children come.

15
00:00:57.080 --> 00:01:00.834
Let your mothers
hear you laugh.

16
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:08.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

17
00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:18.273
Let the grown men come.

18
00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:29.993
Let your wives
and your children...

19
00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:32.395
see you dance.

20
00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:06.798
Women! Women!

21
00:02:06.920 --> 00:02:10.469
I want you to weep!

22
00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:12.397
Just weep...

23
00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:17.231
for the living...

24
00:02:18.760 --> 00:02:20.591
for the dead.

25
00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:25.400
Weep.

26
00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:54.718
Grandma Baby used to say your daddy
was too good for this world.

27
00:02:54.840 --> 00:02:56.637
Remember?

28
00:02:57.720 --> 00:02:59.836
He was a good man.

29
00:02:59.960 --> 00:03:01.871
It scared her.

30
00:03:01.960 --> 00:03:06.556
She used to always fret whether
he wasn't gonna make it through nothin'.

31
00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:08.955
He made it through a lot.

32
00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.793
Maybe Grandma Baby was right.

33
00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:19.471
Denver...

34
00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:23.991
your daddy ain't gonna
never show up here.

35
00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:28.153
- You understand?
- But...

36
00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:33.354
The day ain't gonna
never come...

37
00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:37.393
when Halle knocks on that door.

38
00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:39.311
Never.

39
00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:53.277
There...

40
00:04:01.520 --> 00:04:03.351
Mama!

41
00:04:20.040 --> 00:04:22.076
Paul!

42
00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:24.998
Paul D! Paul D!

43
00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:27.190
You here?

44
00:04:27.320 --> 00:04:31.518
Where else would I be on a Sunday off?

45
00:04:41.320 --> 00:04:44.357
You're here.

46
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:47.357
Uh-huh.

47
00:04:48.600 --> 00:04:50.875
Why don't you come on in here?

48
00:04:54.280 --> 00:04:56.316
Girls right behind me.

49
00:04:56.440 --> 00:04:58.237
I don't hear nobody.

50
00:04:59.840 --> 00:05:02.229
- I gotta cook.
- Me too.

51
00:05:11.320 --> 00:05:13.117
Yeah. yeah.

52
00:05:20.800 --> 00:05:23.360
I thought I'd make
some snap beans.

53
00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:36.308
- Fry up a little corn.
- Yeah.

54
00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:42.874
Paul D. stop it. Stop it.

55
00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:46.714
- Denver?

56
00:05:46.800 --> 00:05:50.395
- Beloved? That you?
- Shh. shh.

57
00:05:50.520 --> 00:05:53.717
- Paul D!

58
00:05:53.800 --> 00:05:55.836
Come on.

59
00:07:58.840 --> 00:08:01.912
That was real fine. Sethe.
Thank you.

60
00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:04.076
- Sure you got enough?
- Yes. ma'am.

61
00:08:04.200 --> 00:08:06.714
Bone-tired and river-whipped.

62
00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:52.629
- Paul D.

63
00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:59.192
Don't tell me I slept
in this chair the whole night.

64
00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:01.669
I'm not gonna say a thing.

65
00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:03.677
- Why you didn't rouse me?
- I did.

66
00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.836
I tried callin' you
two or three times.

67
00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:08.633
- I thought maybe you went out
somewhere.
- Sorry. honey.

68
00:09:08.760 --> 00:09:12.275
- I'll make us some breakfast.
- You know somethin'?

69
00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:14.669
Breakfast can wait.

70
00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:21.632
- Paul! Paul D! Paul D!

71
00:09:21.760 --> 00:09:24.752
What you doin'
in Baby Suggs' bed?

72
00:09:24.840 --> 00:09:26.671
I don't know.

73
00:09:28.120 --> 00:09:30.759
Like I'm havin' house fits.

74
00:09:32.040 --> 00:09:34.634
It got me to move from bed...

75
00:09:34.760 --> 00:09:36.637
to chair to bed.

76
00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:39.951
Slept good though.

77
00:09:41.400 --> 00:09:44.073
No. Come on now.
You gonna be late for work.

78
00:09:44.200 --> 00:09:47.272
Come on. come on.
I got to get to work. So do you.

79
00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:51.717
Come on.

80
00:09:51.840 --> 00:09:54.400
Yeah. right.

81
00:09:54.520 --> 00:09:57.114
- Come on. Beloved.
- Yeah.

82
00:10:17.520 --> 00:10:20.512
Why don't the chickens
have no teeth?

83
00:10:23.360 --> 00:10:26.113
- Whoo!

84
00:10:26.240 --> 00:10:29.710
- Chicken has no teeth.

85
00:10:29.800 --> 00:10:33.270
Mama's cookin' chicken!

86
00:11:02.960 --> 00:11:06.839
Oh. God.

87
00:11:08.880 --> 00:11:10.711
Head hurts.

88
00:12:04.600 --> 00:12:06.875
What you want in here?

89
00:12:14.160 --> 00:12:19.109
I want you touch me...

90
00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:22.232
on the inside part...

91
00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:24.828
and call my name.

92
00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:30.273
Good people take you in.
treat you good...

93
00:12:30.400 --> 00:12:33.278
you oughta try
to be good back.

94
00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:35.510
You don't...

95
00:12:35.640 --> 00:12:37.835
Sethe loves you...

96
00:12:37.960 --> 00:12:40.030
as much as her own daughter.
you know that.

97
00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:42.879
She don't love me
like I love her.

98
00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:45.793
I don't love nobody but her.

99
00:12:45.920 --> 00:12:48.036
Then what you come
in here for?

100
00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:56.710
I want you to touch me
on the inside part.

101
00:12:56.840 --> 00:12:59.991
Go back in that house
and get in that bed.

102
00:13:05.680 --> 00:13:10.231
You has to touch me
on the inside part.

103
00:13:10.320 --> 00:13:13.357
You has to call me my name.

104
00:13:13.480 --> 00:13:15.277
No!

105
00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:17.789
- No.
- I'll go if you call it.

106
00:13:17.920 --> 00:13:21.595
- No. Beloved.
- Please. call it.

107
00:13:23.240 --> 00:13:25.037
Beloved.

108
00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:30.191
Beloved.

109
00:13:34.760 --> 00:13:36.557
Red heart.

110
00:13:37.640 --> 00:13:40.313
Red heart.

111
00:13:40.400 --> 00:13:43.039
Red heart.

112
00:13:43.120 --> 00:13:45.350
Red heart.

113
00:13:45.480 --> 00:13:48.392
Red heart. Red heart.

114
00:13:52.520 --> 00:13:54.909
Red heart.

115
00:13:55.040 --> 00:13:57.793
Red heart. Red heart!

116
00:13:57.920 --> 00:13:59.717
Red heart!

117
00:13:59.840 --> 00:14:02.798
Red heart. Red heart.

118
00:14:21.800 --> 00:14:24.473
Are there flowers in the dark?

119
00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:26.397
There is.

120
00:14:56.560 --> 00:14:58.869
- Come on. Come on.
- Whoo-hoo!

121
00:15:02.920 --> 00:15:06.071
Paul D! Wanna ride with us?

122
00:15:06.160 --> 00:15:09.277
We got the wagon today.
Why don't we...

123
00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:30.872
If I could just tell her.

124
00:15:50.440 --> 00:15:54.069
Now. Sethe. you ain't
gonna like what I'm about to say.

125
00:15:55.760 --> 00:15:58.069
Somethin' is happening to me.

126
00:15:58.160 --> 00:15:59.991
That girl do it.

127
00:16:02.360 --> 00:16:07.195
Fixin' me. Yeah.
She fixed me. Sethe.

128
00:16:07.280 --> 00:16:10.875
She fixed me.
and I can't break it.

129
00:16:10.960 --> 00:16:13.269
She-She moved me
out of the house...

130
00:16:13.400 --> 00:16:16.472
and then she...
she joined me.

131
00:16:16.600 --> 00:16:18.397
No.

132
00:16:20.040 --> 00:16:22.474
- Paul D?

133
00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:24.397
Paul D?

134
00:16:26.080 --> 00:16:28.150
Why. you make me feel
like a young girl...

135
00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:32.119
comin' by to pick me up
after work.

136
00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:35.237
Pupski.
There you go. Pupski.

137
00:16:35.360 --> 00:16:40.434
Better watch out. I might start
lookin' forward to it.

138
00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:42.476
You get off from work
early or what?

139
00:16:44.160 --> 00:16:46.230
I took off early.

140
00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:49.915
- Anything the matter?

141
00:16:50.960 --> 00:16:53.474
In a way of speakin'.

142
00:16:58.520 --> 00:17:02.479
Sethe. you ain't gonna like
what I'm about to say.

143
00:17:04.720 --> 00:17:08.156
Well. say it. Paul D.
whether I like it or not.

144
00:17:12.280 --> 00:17:15.033
I want you pregnant.

145
00:17:24.080 --> 00:17:26.230
You want me pregnant?

146
00:17:28.080 --> 00:17:31.197
Is that what
you come by here for?

147
00:17:31.320 --> 00:17:34.471
Don't you think I'm a little too old
to start that all over again?

148
00:17:34.600 --> 00:17:36.477
Th-Think about it.

149
00:17:45.440 --> 00:17:47.237
You crazy man.

150
00:17:51.040 --> 00:17:52.837
Come on.

151
00:18:06.120 --> 00:18:08.236
What has got into you?

152
00:18:08.360 --> 00:18:12.069
You need some babies
or somebody to play with.

153
00:18:12.200 --> 00:18:16.159
I'm sure willin' to try.
I need a willin' partner though.

154
00:18:16.280 --> 00:18:18.316
I'll say. I'll say.

155
00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:28.717
Mercy.

156
00:18:30.280 --> 00:18:32.794
Let's run. Let's run.

157
00:18:32.880 --> 00:18:35.519
I've been on my feet all day.

158
00:18:35.600 --> 00:18:37.989
Oh. where I been. Sethe?

159
00:18:38.120 --> 00:18:41.317
Stop. Paul D.
My legs ain't made for this.

160
00:18:43.360 --> 00:18:46.477
* Hard work ain't easy *

161
00:18:46.600 --> 00:18:50.479
* Dry bread ain't greasy *

162
00:18:50.600 --> 00:18:53.990
* Little rice. little bean *

163
00:18:54.120 --> 00:18:55.997
Hey. Stamp! Stamp Paid!

164
00:18:56.080 --> 00:18:58.116
I'm gonna take
this one home with me!

165
00:19:02.680 --> 00:19:05.990
Hey. you like this work so much.
maybe you best get in the chute
with the others.

166
00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:08.156
You ain't got much more sense
than they do.

167
00:19:08.240 --> 00:19:10.390
* No meat in between **

168
00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:12.198
I ain't singin' about this!

169
00:19:12.320 --> 00:19:15.437
If a man can make a plan.
the man can make the good times happen.

170
00:19:15.560 --> 00:19:19.872
The man got plans?
You savin' up for a gold mine. boy?

171
00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:23.310
Better than gold. Me and my woman's
plannin' on startin' a family.

172
00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:26.551
Yeah. a new life. Born free!

173
00:19:26.680 --> 00:19:29.274
Now. if that don't mean a good time.
I don't know what does.

174
00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:31.874
Nothin' born free ever again.

175
00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:34.275
What you talkin'?

176
00:19:35.480 --> 00:19:37.948
I been bought and sold
five times.

177
00:19:38.080 --> 00:19:41.356
The last time. to the Northpoint
Bank and Railway Company.

178
00:19:41.480 --> 00:19:45.951
No more! I walk and I sleep
and I eat where I please.

179
00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:48.150
I earn a free man's wage.

180
00:19:48.280 --> 00:19:50.555
Nobody's gonna own us no more.

181
00:19:50.680 --> 00:19:52.955
Nobody's gonna own
my children either.

182
00:19:53.040 --> 00:19:55.508
No more! No more!

183
00:19:55.640 --> 00:19:58.518
Children inherit
where they come from.

184
00:19:58.600 --> 00:20:02.434
Just 'cause you can't see no chains
don't mean they not there.

185
00:20:02.560 --> 00:20:06.838
And as long as the world is white.
that's where we stayin'.

186
00:20:08.120 --> 00:20:10.236
Come on.
Let's go get somethin' to eat.

187
00:20:10.320 --> 00:20:13.118
Come on. Come on.

188
00:20:19.960 --> 00:20:21.916
Mind if I join you?

189
00:20:23.120 --> 00:20:26.032
Free country.
no matter what nobody say.

190
00:20:33.440 --> 00:20:36.193
You don't know. do you. son?

191
00:20:36.320 --> 00:20:38.629
Know what?

192
00:20:39.880 --> 00:20:43.111
You one of Baby Suggs'
Sweet Home men. ain't ya?

193
00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:45.270
Yes. sir.

194
00:20:45.360 --> 00:20:49.638
Me. My brothers.
Her son. Halle.

195
00:20:49.760 --> 00:20:52.194
- You knew Baby?
- Oh. yeah.

196
00:20:52.280 --> 00:20:55.716
Baby Suggs Holy.
God rest her soul.

197
00:20:55.840 --> 00:20:59.389
Yeah. Sethe told me
she died soft as cream.

198
00:20:59.520 --> 00:21:02.592
Well. maybe on the outside.

199
00:21:02.680 --> 00:21:05.194
Why is that?

200
00:21:20.080 --> 00:21:25.154
It was me who had brung Sethe across the
river when she run away from Sweet Home.

201
00:21:27.880 --> 00:21:31.111
I was there the day it happened.

202
00:21:36.240 --> 00:21:38.549
Who is it?

203
00:21:38.640 --> 00:21:41.632
That there's a picture of Sethe.

204
00:21:41.720 --> 00:21:43.551
Sethe?

205
00:21:45.560 --> 00:21:48.358
That ain't her mouth.

206
00:21:48.480 --> 00:21:51.597
I can see
why you may think it...

207
00:21:51.720 --> 00:21:54.075
around the eyes.

208
00:21:56.640 --> 00:22:00.189
B-But that there
ain't her mouth.

209
00:22:02.720 --> 00:22:07.714
Besides. why would they put some
coloured woman's picture in the paper?

210
00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:10.638
You don't read. do you. son?

211
00:22:16.600 --> 00:22:20.195
You want me to read to you?

212
00:23:01.080 --> 00:23:05.198
Already fed the girls.
You eat?

213
00:23:06.880 --> 00:23:09.474
Want something?

214
00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:36.199
Best you come inside.

215
00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:57.836
I don't have to tell you
about Sweet Home...

216
00:23:57.960 --> 00:23:59.757
what it was.

217
00:24:01.360 --> 00:24:06.275
Maybe you don't know what it was like
for me to get away from there.

218
00:24:07.400 --> 00:24:10.710
I did it.
I got us all out.

219
00:24:10.800 --> 00:24:15.078
Up until then. it was the only thing
I ever did on my own.

220
00:24:15.160 --> 00:24:18.630
Me... usin' my own head.

221
00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:24.318
But it was more than that.

222
00:24:25.600 --> 00:24:28.319
I was... I was big...

223
00:24:28.400 --> 00:24:30.709
and wide. Paul.

224
00:24:30.800 --> 00:24:36.033
So wide. when I stretched out my arms.
all my children could get in between.

225
00:24:36.160 --> 00:24:39.869
Looked like I... Looked like I loved 'em
more after we got here.

226
00:24:41.880 --> 00:24:46.271
Maybe I just knew that long as we was
in Kentucky with Schoolteacher...

227
00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:49.153
they really wasn't mine to love.

228
00:24:49.280 --> 00:24:52.033
Look like when
I jumped off that wagon...

229
00:24:52.120 --> 00:24:56.636
wasn't nobody in this world
I couldn't love if I want to.

230
00:24:58.240 --> 00:25:00.595
Twenty-eight days.

231
00:25:00.720 --> 00:25:04.554
Twenty-eight good days
of free life.

232
00:25:05.640 --> 00:25:08.279
I'd wake up in the morning and...

233
00:25:08.400 --> 00:25:12.313
decide for myself
what to do with the day.

234
00:25:14.040 --> 00:25:16.838
Sometimes I...
I hear my boys...

235
00:25:16.920 --> 00:25:20.708
hear 'em laughin' a laugh
I ain't never heard.

236
00:25:20.840 --> 00:25:24.355
First I get scared. scared
somebody might hear 'em...

237
00:25:24.480 --> 00:25:26.596
and get mad.

238
00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:30.269
Then I remembered that if they laughed
that hard till it hurt...

239
00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:33.676
that'd be the only hurt
they have all day.

240
00:25:35.480 --> 00:25:38.119
And when the people
would gather...

241
00:25:38.200 --> 00:25:41.636
they'd come from all around
to hear Baby Suggs Holy...

242
00:25:41.720 --> 00:25:46.077
I seen and heard things
I ain't never seen before.

243
00:25:48.840 --> 00:25:52.958
I seen what free Negroes
look like for the first time.

244
00:25:54.680 --> 00:25:59.549
Here in this place.
we are flesh.

245
00:25:59.680 --> 00:26:02.717
Flesh that weeps...

246
00:26:02.800 --> 00:26:04.631
laughs...

247
00:26:04.720 --> 00:26:07.439
dances barefoot
in the grass.

248
00:26:10.480 --> 00:26:13.870
Love your flesh.

249
00:26:14.960 --> 00:26:17.315
Love it hard.

250
00:26:17.440 --> 00:26:22.833
Yonder...
they do not love our flesh.

251
00:26:22.960 --> 00:26:25.190
Amen.

252
00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:30.910
Oh. my people...

253
00:26:32.520 --> 00:26:36.149
they do not love your hands.

254
00:26:38.000 --> 00:26:43.313
Those... they only use...

255
00:26:43.440 --> 00:26:46.671
tie... bind...

256
00:26:46.800 --> 00:26:49.030
chop off...

257
00:26:49.160 --> 00:26:51.799
and leave empty.

258
00:26:54.360 --> 00:26:57.318
Love your hands.

259
00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:03.234
Raise them up...

260
00:27:03.320 --> 00:27:06.118
and kiss them.

261
00:27:16.160 --> 00:27:20.517
Twenty-eight days of... freedom.

262
00:27:22.440 --> 00:27:25.318
On the 29th day. it was over.

263
00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:38.915
Outside.

264
00:28:14.240 --> 00:28:18.870
There's a look that white folks get.

265
00:28:18.960 --> 00:28:23.078
Righteous look that's like
a flag goin' up a pole.

266
00:28:25.600 --> 00:28:28.114
A righteousness that...

267
00:28:28.240 --> 00:28:31.312
comes along with the whip
and the fist...

268
00:28:31.440 --> 00:28:34.750
the burnin'. the lie.

269
00:28:34.880 --> 00:28:37.952
Long before it happens
in the open.

270
00:28:38.080 --> 00:28:41.117
No. no!

271
00:28:41.200 --> 00:28:45.113
- Howard. Buglar. get in the shed!

272
00:28:45.200 --> 00:28:48.829
Get in the shed! Run!

273
00:28:52.320 --> 00:28:54.788
No!

274
00:28:54.920 --> 00:28:57.957
Get in the shed! No!

275
00:28:59.720 --> 00:29:04.840
No! No! No! No!

276
00:29:13.800 --> 00:29:18.874
No. no. no!

277
00:29:18.960 --> 00:29:22.953
- No. no. no!
- Mama!

278
00:29:25.880 --> 00:29:28.314
Mama!

279
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:41.350
- Sethe! Sethe! No!

280
00:29:41.480 --> 00:29:45.109
- Sethe!

281
00:29:50.120 --> 00:29:52.236
God Almighty.

282
00:30:01.080 --> 00:30:03.913
What'd you go
and do that for?

283
00:30:04.040 --> 00:30:06.952
What'd you go
and do that for?

284
00:30:12.400 --> 00:30:15.233
What'd you go
and do that for?

285
00:30:32.200 --> 00:30:36.671
Y'all better go on.
Nothin' here to claim. I guess.

286
00:30:36.800 --> 00:30:40.236
- Look like your business is over.

287
00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:43.391
Mine's started.

288
00:30:46.360 --> 00:30:48.555
Animal.

289
00:31:01.840 --> 00:31:04.673
Oh.

290
00:31:04.760 --> 00:31:06.591
Oh.

291
00:31:09.200 --> 00:31:13.352
- Oh.
- I'm going out. I'll send for a wagon.

292
00:31:14.480 --> 00:31:17.836
Howard. Howard!

293
00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:21.032
- Wake up. Buglar. Baby!

294
00:31:21.160 --> 00:31:23.549
Come on. sweetheart.
Wake up! Wake up!

295
00:31:23.680 --> 00:31:25.796
- Oh!

296
00:31:25.920 --> 00:31:28.036
I beg your pardon.

297
00:31:28.160 --> 00:31:32.358
Sethe. you take my armload
and give me your'n.

298
00:31:37.120 --> 00:31:42.240
I beg your pardon. I beg your pardon.

299
00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:45.198
I beg your pardon.

300
00:31:47.240 --> 00:31:49.913
Your love
is too thick. Sethe.

301
00:31:51.400 --> 00:31:54.597
Love is or it isn't. Paul D.

302
00:31:54.680 --> 00:31:57.433
Thin love
ain't no love at all.

303
00:31:57.520 --> 00:31:59.875
I stopped him.

304
00:31:59.960 --> 00:32:03.236
I put my babies
where'd they be safe.

305
00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:06.557
Didn't work. though. did it?

306
00:32:06.640 --> 00:32:09.757
Your boys are gone.
you don't know where.

307
00:32:09.840 --> 00:32:15.153
One girl's dead. The other
can't get further than the yard.

308
00:32:16.400 --> 00:32:18.595
How did it work?

309
00:32:19.800 --> 00:32:22.189
They ain't at Sweet Home.

310
00:32:22.320 --> 00:32:24.959
Schoolteacher ain't got 'em.

311
00:32:25.040 --> 00:32:29.591
- Maybe there's worse.
- It ain't my job to know
what's worse. Paul D.

312
00:32:29.680 --> 00:32:34.435
It's my job to know what is and
keep my children away from it.
'cause I'd rather know...

313
00:32:34.560 --> 00:32:38.235
they at peace in heaven than live in
a hell here on Earth. so help me. Jesus.

314
00:32:38.320 --> 00:32:41.630
- What you did was wrong. Sethe.
- I should've gone back there?

315
00:32:41.720 --> 00:32:44.996
Took my babies
back to Sweet Home?

316
00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:47.275
There could've been a way.
Some other way.

317
00:32:47.400 --> 00:32:49.277
What way. Paul D?

318
00:32:49.360 --> 00:32:52.830
You got two feet.
Sethe. not four.

319
00:33:01.280 --> 00:33:03.874
You can set aside supper for me.

320
00:33:08.560 --> 00:33:11.870
I might be late gettin' back.

321
00:33:15.240 --> 00:33:18.755
After all
I just told you. Paul D...

322
00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:24.549
and after you tellin' me
how many feet I got...

323
00:33:24.680 --> 00:33:28.992
you think sayin' goodbye
is gonna break me into pieces?

324
00:33:35.640 --> 00:33:38.108
You're a sweet man.

325
00:33:51.480 --> 00:33:54.040
So long. Paul D.

326
00:34:10.920 --> 00:34:13.150
We could roast some taters.

327
00:34:13.280 --> 00:34:16.795
Too late. Tomorrow.

328
00:34:58.160 --> 00:35:00.993
I made that song up.

329
00:35:01.080 --> 00:35:04.789
I made it up and sang it
to my children.

330
00:35:04.880 --> 00:35:07.713
Nobody knows that song but...

331
00:35:08.920 --> 00:35:11.229
me and my children.

332
00:35:12.680 --> 00:35:15.148
I know.

333
00:36:19.600 --> 00:36:22.319
You came back to me.

334
00:36:25.440 --> 00:36:27.715
Yeah.

335
00:37:06.320 --> 00:37:10.791
- Ohh.

336
00:37:10.920 --> 00:37:13.832
- Back stiff?
- Mmm. Yeah.

337
00:37:15.800 --> 00:37:19.349
- Sleeping on the floor's supposed
to be good for you.
- Hurt like the devil.

338
00:37:19.440 --> 00:37:22.034
Should I wake her?

339
00:37:22.160 --> 00:37:24.594
No. Let her rest.

340
00:37:24.720 --> 00:37:26.995
She likes to see you off
in the morning.

341
00:37:27.120 --> 00:37:29.998
I'm gonna let her. but first
get me that ham out of there.

342
00:37:30.120 --> 00:37:34.591
I'm gonna make us a nice.
big breakfast against the cold outside.

343
00:37:34.720 --> 00:37:37.951
- Won't you be late for work?
- First time I'll be late in 16 years.

344
00:37:38.040 --> 00:37:39.871
It don't matter.

345
00:37:39.960 --> 00:37:43.555
Whatever goes on out there goes on
with or without me showin' up on time.

346
00:37:43.640 --> 00:37:45.790
The world is right here
in this room.

347
00:37:45.920 --> 00:37:50.436
- Right here is all that is
and all there needs to be.

348
00:37:50.560 --> 00:37:55.634
- She ain't even mad at me. Not a bit.

349
00:38:15.120 --> 00:38:17.350
Whoo.

350
00:38:31.840 --> 00:38:34.957
- Mama!
- Mama!

351
00:38:38.120 --> 00:38:39.917
- Mama!
- Mama!

352
00:38:44.920 --> 00:38:47.309
- Mama!
- Mama!

353
00:39:06.440 --> 00:39:08.908
Put it back in there.
Put it back.

354
00:39:09.040 --> 00:39:11.679
That's it. You're late. You're fired.

355
00:39:11.760 --> 00:39:13.876
That's all.
I-I... I've had it.

356
00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:16.912
You make potato salad
always too sweet.

357
00:39:17.040 --> 00:39:19.429
And you didn't make
the pies today.

358
00:39:19.560 --> 00:39:23.030
You take home too much food. Where
are you going? Where are you going?

359
00:40:11.560 --> 00:40:15.348
- My goodness. Is that...
- Yes. it is.

360
00:40:20.360 --> 00:40:23.636
- Did you see that?
- What? That's a disgrace.

361
00:40:32.720 --> 00:40:34.756
Sethe.

362
00:40:34.880 --> 00:40:38.555
Don't look now. but there is Sethe.

363
00:40:48.320 --> 00:40:50.470
- Mm.
- Is she the one?

364
00:41:07.160 --> 00:41:09.958
Will that be all. ma'am?

365
00:41:12.640 --> 00:41:14.437
- * To get my grip *

366
00:41:14.560 --> 00:41:18.599
* I came back home just a-pullin'
the skiff. just a-pullin' the skiff *

367
00:41:18.720 --> 00:41:21.439
* Went upstairs to make my bed *

368
00:41:21.520 --> 00:41:24.432
* I made a mistake
and bumped my head *

369
00:41:24.560 --> 00:41:27.472
* Just a-pullin' the skiff
Just a-pullin' the skiff *

370
00:41:27.600 --> 00:41:30.751
* I came downstairs to milk that cow *

371
00:41:30.880 --> 00:41:33.678
* I made a mistake
and I milked that sow *

372
00:41:33.800 --> 00:41:37.713
* Just a-pullin' the skiff
Just a-pullin' the skiff *

373
00:41:37.840 --> 00:41:40.035
- * Tomorrow. tomorrow
tomorrow never comes *

374
00:41:40.160 --> 00:41:43.391
* Tomorrow. tomorrow
tomorrow never comes *

375
00:41:43.480 --> 00:41:46.517
- The best part.

376
00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:53.476
- Look at my pretty baby.
She's my best thing.
- Denver.

377
00:41:53.560 --> 00:41:56.199
* Tomorrow never come *

378
00:41:56.280 --> 00:41:59.670
- Thank you. Mama.
- * Tomorrow. tomorrow
tomorrow in the barn **

379
00:42:29.480 --> 00:42:31.277
This one?

380
00:42:31.400 --> 00:42:34.710
- Would you wrap it. please?
- What's she doing?

381
00:42:50.680 --> 00:42:53.274
The first day we got here
to Bluestone Road...

382
00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:55.920
you dribbled clear spit
on my face.

383
00:42:56.040 --> 00:43:00.716
Just like when you come back and drink
that water. it run down your chin.

384
00:43:00.840 --> 00:43:03.149
I'd have recognized you
right off...

385
00:43:03.280 --> 00:43:05.794
- But Paul D. he distract me.

386
00:43:05.920 --> 00:43:07.876
Then later on...

387
00:43:07.960 --> 00:43:12.351
when you asked me about them earrings
I used to dangle for you to play with...

388
00:43:12.440 --> 00:43:15.273
- I'd have known that was you...

389
00:43:15.400 --> 00:43:17.197
except for Paul D.

390
00:43:19.120 --> 00:43:21.759
Looked to me like he wanted you out
from the beginning.

391
00:43:21.840 --> 00:43:25.150
But I wouldn't let him.
What you think?

392
00:43:25.240 --> 00:43:27.071
Hmm.

393
00:43:27.160 --> 00:43:31.790
I mean. look how he run off first
he hear about you and me in the shed.

394
00:43:33.160 --> 00:43:35.754
Too tough for him
to even listen to.

395
00:43:36.840 --> 00:43:40.230
"My love too thick." he said.

396
00:43:40.360 --> 00:43:42.954
What do he know about it?

397
00:43:43.080 --> 00:43:45.310
* High Johnny *

398
00:43:46.200 --> 00:43:47.633
* Wide Johnny *

399
00:43:47.760 --> 00:43:51.469
* Don't you leave my side *

400
00:43:51.600 --> 00:43:54.592
* High Johnny *

401
00:43:54.720 --> 00:43:57.359
* Wide Johnny *

402
00:43:57.480 --> 00:44:02.759
* Sweet William. bend down low *

403
00:44:05.440 --> 00:44:09.592
- * Jack. we raise up high *

404
00:44:09.680 --> 00:44:13.673
- * Lambs wool **
- Why you hurt me?

405
00:44:13.800 --> 00:44:17.509
Baby. you know.

406
00:44:17.640 --> 00:44:19.870
Why you leave me?

407
00:44:21.040 --> 00:44:23.600
Beloved. I wasn't never
gonna leave you.

408
00:44:23.720 --> 00:44:25.517
Never.

409
00:44:25.640 --> 00:44:28.950
But there wasn't no way I was gonna let
Schoolteacher come haul all of us off...

410
00:44:29.040 --> 00:44:31.713
and measure your behind
'fore he tore it up.

411
00:44:31.840 --> 00:44:35.276
- You leave me.
- No. baby. No.

412
00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:40.110
See. my plan was to get us all over
to the other side where my own mammy is.

413
00:44:40.240 --> 00:44:43.073
They stopped me from gettin' us
all there. but you had to be put...

414
00:44:43.200 --> 00:44:45.873
where you'd be safe.
and I did that.

415
00:44:46.920 --> 00:44:48.911
Now you come back...

416
00:44:49.040 --> 00:44:51.793
and baby. I ain't gonna
never let you go.

417
00:44:51.920 --> 00:44:53.717
I want a sweet.

418
00:44:53.840 --> 00:44:56.274
Sweet?

419
00:44:56.400 --> 00:44:58.755
Sweet.

420
00:44:58.840 --> 00:45:01.229
We don't have nothin' sweet
no more. baby.

421
00:45:01.360 --> 00:45:04.591
Why you don't let me
eat the pie no more?

422
00:45:07.040 --> 00:45:10.828
- Since Mama spent all the money.
we don't have no more.

423
00:45:10.960 --> 00:45:14.589
I want a sweet! I want a sweet!

424
00:45:14.720 --> 00:45:18.030
- Sweet. sweet. sweet!
- Beloved? Beloved!

425
00:45:18.160 --> 00:45:21.675
- Beloved. baby?

426
00:45:21.800 --> 00:45:23.950
Baby? Beloved!

427
00:45:30.320 --> 00:45:32.550
It's all right.

428
00:45:35.120 --> 00:45:39.159
- I understand.

429
00:46:36.880 --> 00:46:38.677
Beloved?

430
00:48:07.880 --> 00:48:09.677
Mama!

431
00:48:12.120 --> 00:48:15.476
- Mama!

432
00:48:32.720 --> 00:48:34.551
Mama!

433
00:48:40.120 --> 00:48:41.951
Mama!

434
00:48:45.840 --> 00:48:47.671
Mama!

435
00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:06.112
You best leave
that quilt alone.

436
00:49:07.160 --> 00:49:09.469
That's Grandma's quilt.

437
00:49:22.240 --> 00:49:26.392
I want a sweet. Where is sweet?

438
00:50:03.600 --> 00:50:08.276
You mean I never
tell you about your daddy. Halle?

439
00:50:08.400 --> 00:50:12.279
How he bought my freedom
with all that toil...

440
00:50:12.400 --> 00:50:16.188
and never had a chance to see
the promised land for hisself?

441
00:50:17.840 --> 00:50:21.913
Didn't I tell you
about the Bodwins...

442
00:50:22.000 --> 00:50:24.560
who find me this here house...

443
00:50:24.680 --> 00:50:27.399
and give me work in theirs?

444
00:50:27.520 --> 00:50:32.469
How the Bodwins. they saved
your Mama's neck from the rope.

445
00:50:33.520 --> 00:50:37.752
I never tell you all this?

446
00:50:37.840 --> 00:50:41.150
Is that why you scared...

447
00:50:41.240 --> 00:50:44.471
to go down them steps
and out yonder...

448
00:50:44.560 --> 00:50:47.313
by yourself?

449
00:50:47.440 --> 00:50:50.591
Is that why you didn't go back
to Miss Lady...

450
00:50:50.720 --> 00:50:52.995
and finish learnin'
your letters?

451
00:50:53.080 --> 00:50:56.993
You liked going there.
I remember.

452
00:50:57.080 --> 00:51:02.154
Bein' with the other children.
All of a sudden you've stopped.

453
00:51:05.280 --> 00:51:07.555
There was this boy...

454
00:51:09.200 --> 00:51:11.998
and he said things about Mama.

455
00:51:12.080 --> 00:51:15.038
- He said he could prove it.

456
00:51:15.120 --> 00:51:18.590
My Jesus. my.

457
00:51:20.440 --> 00:51:22.749
Come here. child.

458
00:51:30.400 --> 00:51:33.119
We got to go sometime.

459
00:51:33.200 --> 00:51:38.149
You got to go out yonder
by yourself sometime.

460
00:51:40.240 --> 00:51:43.471
You got to go on
out of the yard.

461
00:51:43.600 --> 00:51:45.955
Go on.

462
00:53:17.960 --> 00:53:20.155
Come on. now.

463
00:53:32.120 --> 00:53:34.156
I want to work. Miss Lady.

464
00:53:35.160 --> 00:53:36.991
Work?

465
00:53:37.080 --> 00:53:40.470
Start learnin'
your letters again?

466
00:53:42.960 --> 00:53:45.315
I mean "work" work.

467
00:53:47.280 --> 00:53:49.111
Well. Denver...

468
00:53:50.280 --> 00:53:52.635
what can you do?

469
00:53:57.760 --> 00:54:00.320
I can't do nothin'.

470
00:54:00.400 --> 00:54:04.439
But I could learn it for you...
if you have a little extra.

471
00:54:06.720 --> 00:54:08.517
Extra?

472
00:54:11.240 --> 00:54:13.037
Food.

473
00:54:18.040 --> 00:54:19.871
My mama...

474
00:54:21.760 --> 00:54:24.638
she don't feel too good.

475
00:54:25.760 --> 00:54:28.354
Oh. baby.

476
00:54:43.120 --> 00:54:46.590
Eat. Bad Sethe.

477
00:54:46.680 --> 00:54:49.672
Yes. Bad Sethe.

478
00:54:58.480 --> 00:55:01.756
Eat.

479
00:55:01.840 --> 00:55:03.717
Eat.

480
00:55:36.640 --> 00:55:39.279
Ohh. honey.

481
00:55:39.400 --> 00:55:41.197
What you got?

482
00:55:57.320 --> 00:55:59.788
- Thank you. ma'am.

483
00:55:59.920 --> 00:56:02.673
You're more than welcome.
my child.

484
00:56:17.560 --> 00:56:19.391
Thank you.

485
00:56:21.800 --> 00:56:25.031
No. no. That's not my bowl.

486
00:56:25.160 --> 00:56:27.196
Sugar. mine got
a blue ring on it.

487
00:56:27.280 --> 00:56:29.475
You wanna come in a spell?
Come on in.

488
00:56:29.600 --> 00:56:33.718
- I got some warm gingerbread.
You just go on in there.
- Okay.

489
00:57:12.880 --> 00:57:17.351
Shh. Shh. Go on.
Move. Get off of me.

490
00:57:17.480 --> 00:57:21.393
- You stink. and you messin'
up my dress. Stop it.

491
00:57:21.520 --> 00:57:24.193
I'm tellin' you. get off of me.
Get off of me. now!

492
00:57:24.320 --> 00:57:26.788
- Stop it.

493
00:57:26.920 --> 00:57:30.037
- How far you goin'. miss?
- I goin' to Cincinnati.

494
00:57:35.120 --> 00:57:39.750
- That's as far as
we're goin'. miss. Get off.
- Thank you.

495
00:57:41.600 --> 00:57:44.797
- How's it goin'?
- Take care of yourself. all right?

496
00:57:44.880 --> 00:57:48.395
Excuse me. I was lookin'
for the Bodwin's house.

497
00:57:48.520 --> 00:57:52.513
You bugger off. you hear me?

498
00:58:07.760 --> 00:58:09.557
Yes?

499
00:58:13.760 --> 00:58:15.955
What you want?

500
00:58:18.640 --> 00:58:23.270
I wanted to see Mr and Mrs Bowman...
Mr and Mrs Bodwin.

501
00:58:23.400 --> 00:58:25.630
Ms Bodwin.

502
00:58:25.720 --> 00:58:29.474
They brother and sister. darlin'.
What you want with 'em?

503
00:58:29.600 --> 00:58:35.038
I was lookin' for work. and I thought
that they might know about some.

504
00:58:36.400 --> 00:58:38.755
Ohh...

505
00:58:38.840 --> 00:58:41.752
you Baby Suggs' kid. ain't you?

506
00:58:41.840 --> 00:58:46.277
- Yes'm.
- I heard your mother took sick.

507
00:58:46.400 --> 00:58:50.029
- Is that so?
- Yes'm.

508
00:58:51.360 --> 00:58:55.148
Well. come on in.
You're lettin' in flies. Come on.

509
00:58:57.720 --> 00:59:02.475
You know what? I been here since I'm
14. and I can remember like yesterday...

510
00:59:02.600 --> 00:59:06.752
when Baby Suggs Holy came here
and sat right where you are.

511
00:59:06.840 --> 00:59:11.436
White man. name of Garner. brought her.
He and Mr Bodwin was good friends.

512
00:59:11.560 --> 00:59:16.270
- That's how she got that house
you all live in. Other things too.
- Yes'm.

513
00:59:16.400 --> 00:59:20.791
I never went to those woodland services.
but she was always nice to me.

514
00:59:20.880 --> 00:59:24.236
Always.
Never be another like her.

515
00:59:24.360 --> 00:59:26.430
I miss her.

516
00:59:26.560 --> 00:59:31.395
Bet you do. Everybody miss her.
That was a good woman.

517
00:59:33.200 --> 00:59:35.077
Well...

518
00:59:35.160 --> 00:59:39.995
I don't know whether the Bodwins
think so or not. but they sure
could use some extra help.

519
00:59:40.080 --> 00:59:42.469
- You think?

520
00:59:42.600 --> 00:59:45.831
Especially at night.
when it's no good for me to come.

521
00:59:45.960 --> 00:59:49.919
It'll take some convincin'.
but maybe you could come after supper.

522
00:59:50.000 --> 00:59:53.959
Take care of your mama
during the day. How's that?

523
00:59:54.080 --> 00:59:57.072
- Fine.

524
00:59:57.200 --> 00:59:58.997
But what would I do
at night?

525
00:59:59.120 --> 01:00:03.159
- Just be here in case.
- In case what?

526
01:00:03.280 --> 01:00:08.229
In case the house burned down or
bad weather slopped the roads up
so bad I can't get here on time.

527
01:00:08.360 --> 01:00:10.430
Or late guests needed
cleanin' up after.

528
01:00:10.520 --> 01:00:12.511
Anything.

529
01:00:12.600 --> 01:00:16.559
Don't ask me
what white folks need at night.

530
01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:21.151
- They good white folk?
- Oh. yeah. They good.

531
01:00:21.280 --> 01:00:25.353
Can't say they ain't good.
I wouldn't trade 'em
for another pair. I tell you that.

532
01:00:25.480 --> 01:00:30.600
But you come back in a few days.
Give me a chance to lead up to it.

533
01:00:30.720 --> 01:00:33.075
All right?

534
01:00:36.640 --> 01:00:39.108
What is it. child?

535
01:00:40.240 --> 01:00:43.437
What's the trouble with Sethe?

536
01:00:51.280 --> 01:00:53.919
Is it really the daughter. Janey?
The killed one?

537
01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:56.230
That's what the girl say.

538
01:00:56.360 --> 01:00:59.796
- How do you know it's her?
- It's sittin' there. Lucille.

539
01:00:59.920 --> 01:01:02.514
It sleeps. eats and raises hell.

540
01:01:02.640 --> 01:01:05.393
- I'll be. A baby.

541
01:01:05.520 --> 01:01:09.274
Nah. It's grown. It's the age
it would've been had it lived.

542
01:01:09.360 --> 01:01:12.158
- Mercy.
- What you talkin' about?
You talkin' about flesh?

543
01:01:12.240 --> 01:01:16.472
- I'm talkin' about flesh...
and it's whoopin' her...

544
01:01:16.560 --> 01:01:18.391
like she was batter.

545
01:01:18.480 --> 01:01:23.679
- I guess she had it comin' a little.
- Nobody got that comin'.

546
01:01:23.760 --> 01:01:28.515
But Ella. you just don't up
and kill your children.

547
01:01:28.640 --> 01:01:32.872
No. and the children can't just up
and kill the mama.

548
01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:36.197
Them that die bad
don't stay in the ground.

549
01:01:52.040 --> 01:01:54.554
Schoolteacher...

550
01:01:54.640 --> 01:01:56.471
Mama?

551
01:01:57.640 --> 01:02:00.552
Nobody ain't makin' nothin'.

552
01:02:00.680 --> 01:02:03.513
- Nobody.
- Mama. I'm going out now.

553
01:02:08.400 --> 01:02:11.915
I got a job workin' nights
over at the Bodwins.

554
01:02:13.120 --> 01:02:16.237
Mr Bodwin's coming
to pick me up now.

555
01:02:18.280 --> 01:02:21.829
Writin' my baby's
characteristics!

556
01:02:21.960 --> 01:02:23.996
Lay that down.

557
01:02:24.080 --> 01:02:27.038
We have money now.

558
01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:33.752
Mama!

559
01:03:04.040 --> 01:03:05.837
Hey.

560
01:04:21.840 --> 01:04:24.149
It's comin' out. It's over.

561
01:04:46.440 --> 01:04:49.830
- Help us. help us.

562
01:04:49.960 --> 01:04:51.757
Ohh!

563
01:04:51.880 --> 01:04:54.269
Ohh. amen!

564
01:04:59.760 --> 01:05:03.355
- Help us. Jesus!

565
01:05:09.200 --> 01:05:12.112
Jesus. Jesus. Jesus.

566
01:05:12.240 --> 01:05:14.629
- * I heard the voice *
- Yes.

567
01:05:14.760 --> 01:05:18.116
- I heard the voice.
- * I heard the voice *

568
01:05:18.240 --> 01:05:22.677
- I heard the voice.
- * I heard the voice *

569
01:05:24.640 --> 01:05:28.110
* I heard the voice say *

570
01:05:28.240 --> 01:05:32.791
* Come unto me and rest *

571
01:05:32.880 --> 01:05:36.190
* I *

572
01:05:36.320 --> 01:05:39.392
- * Heard *
- * The voice *

573
01:05:39.520 --> 01:05:42.432
* The *

574
01:05:42.560 --> 01:05:45.279
* Voice *

575
01:05:45.360 --> 01:05:49.035
* Of *

576
01:05:49.160 --> 01:05:54.678
- * Jesus *

577
01:05:54.800 --> 01:05:57.997
* Say *

578
01:05:58.120 --> 01:06:00.236
* Come *

579
01:06:00.360 --> 01:06:06.595
* Un-to *

580
01:06:06.720 --> 01:06:10.349
* Me *

581
01:06:10.480 --> 01:06:13.233
* And *

582
01:06:13.360 --> 01:06:16.670
* Rest *

583
01:06:16.800 --> 01:06:20.031
- * Lay down. thou weary one *
- It's all right.

584
01:06:20.160 --> 01:06:25.792
* Lay down thy head
upon my breast *

585
01:06:25.880 --> 01:06:29.350
* Lay *

586
01:06:29.480 --> 01:06:32.040
* Down *

587
01:06:32.160 --> 01:06:35.311
* Thou *

588
01:06:35.440 --> 01:06:41.709
* Weary *

589
01:06:41.840 --> 01:06:44.638
* One *

590
01:06:44.720 --> 01:06:47.109
- Mama?
- * Lay *

591
01:06:47.240 --> 01:06:49.708
- * Down *

592
01:06:56.360 --> 01:06:59.955
- * I came to Jesus *

593
01:07:00.080 --> 01:07:02.799
- Oh. Lord. please.
- * As I was *

594
01:07:02.920 --> 01:07:06.595
* The weary one who said *

595
01:07:06.720 --> 01:07:10.395
* I *

596
01:07:10.480 --> 01:07:13.074
* Came *

597
01:07:13.200 --> 01:07:15.760
* To *

598
01:07:15.880 --> 01:07:22.479
* Je-sus *

599
01:07:22.600 --> 01:07:25.433
* As *

600
01:07:25.520 --> 01:07:29.035
* I *

601
01:07:29.160 --> 01:07:31.116
* Was *

602
01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:35.909
* He *

603
01:07:37.200 --> 01:07:41.955
* Had *

604
01:07:42.080 --> 01:07:46.631
* Hold and *

605
01:07:48.200 --> 01:07:50.031
- * Said *
- No.

606
01:07:50.160 --> 01:07:52.116
- No. no. no. no.
- * Tilt your eyes down low *

607
01:07:52.240 --> 01:07:54.196
No. no. no. no.

608
01:07:58.760 --> 01:08:00.910
- Mama?
- * I **

609
01:08:01.040 --> 01:08:03.759
Mama?

610
01:08:03.880 --> 01:08:06.917
- Mama. that's Mr Bodwin!

611
01:08:07.040 --> 01:08:09.998
- Mama!

612
01:08:10.120 --> 01:08:12.588
Mama!

613
01:08:14.160 --> 01:08:18.039
- Mama!
- No. no. no! No. no. no!

614
01:08:18.160 --> 01:08:23.075
- No!
- Mama! Mama!

615
01:10:14.440 --> 01:10:17.238
Paul D? Is that you?

616
01:10:22.880 --> 01:10:24.950
Good morning.

617
01:10:25.040 --> 01:10:28.555
Well. it is now.

618
01:10:30.880 --> 01:10:34.031
- How you gettin' along?
- Don't pay to complain.

619
01:10:34.160 --> 01:10:37.311
- Yeah. Right. You on your way home?
- No.

620
01:10:37.440 --> 01:10:40.113
I got an afternoon job
at the shirt factory.

621
01:10:40.240 --> 01:10:43.312
I figure between that
and my night work at the Bodwins...

622
01:10:43.440 --> 01:10:46.352
I might be able to put
somethin' aside for me and Mama.

623
01:10:46.480 --> 01:10:50.109
- They treatin' you right
over at the Bodwins?
- Mm-hmm. More than all right.

624
01:10:50.240 --> 01:10:52.834
Ms Bodwin. she teachin' me stuff.
Book stuff.

625
01:10:52.960 --> 01:10:55.110
She say I might go
to Oberlin College.

626
01:10:55.200 --> 01:10:58.237
That's fine. mighty fine.

627
01:11:00.920 --> 01:11:02.751
Well.

628
01:11:02.880 --> 01:11:05.997
Your mother all right?

629
01:11:10.800 --> 01:11:15.237
No. She's not a bit all right.

630
01:11:15.360 --> 01:11:19.194
She hasn't gotten out of bed
since that day.

631
01:11:21.280 --> 01:11:25.034
Think I should stop by?
Think she'd welcome it?

632
01:11:27.200 --> 01:11:29.475
I don't know.

633
01:11:31.520 --> 01:11:34.876
I think I lost my mama.
Paul D.

634
01:11:37.520 --> 01:11:40.353
Th-That girl.
You know. Beloved.

635
01:11:41.960 --> 01:11:45.191
She-She gone like they say?

636
01:11:45.280 --> 01:11:48.590
Haven't seen her since that day.

637
01:11:48.720 --> 01:11:52.633
Mama say she gone.
She can feel it.

638
01:11:52.760 --> 01:11:56.275
You think she sure enough
your sister?

639
01:11:57.440 --> 01:11:59.271
At times.

640
01:12:00.360 --> 01:12:02.510
At other times...

641
01:12:05.080 --> 01:12:06.877
I think she was more.

642
01:12:10.720 --> 01:12:14.076
But who would know that
better than you. Paul D?

643
01:12:14.200 --> 01:12:16.953
You sure enough knew her.

644
01:12:17.080 --> 01:12:20.629
- Well. if you want my opinion...
- I don't.

645
01:12:20.760 --> 01:12:23.069
I have my own.

646
01:12:23.200 --> 01:12:25.714
- You grown.

647
01:12:25.840 --> 01:12:27.637
Yes. sir.

648
01:12:30.800 --> 01:12:34.031
Well. good luck with your job.

649
01:12:34.160 --> 01:12:36.355
Thank you.

650
01:12:41.440 --> 01:12:43.271
Bye. now.

651
01:12:43.360 --> 01:12:46.193
Watch your step.

652
01:12:51.680 --> 01:12:53.716
Paul D?

653
01:12:56.160 --> 01:12:57.957
You don't have to stay away.

654
01:12:59.920 --> 01:13:02.798
But you watch how you talk
to my mama. you hear?

655
01:13:02.880 --> 01:13:04.996
Don't worry.

656
01:13:07.520 --> 01:13:10.592
Hey. Miss Denver!
Wait up!

657
01:13:10.720 --> 01:13:12.915
Hi.

658
01:13:19.200 --> 01:13:21.031
Watch it. miss.

659
01:13:29.200 --> 01:13:31.475
Yeah.

660
01:13:32.880 --> 01:13:34.677
Ohh.

661
01:14:44.120 --> 01:14:45.917
Sethe?

662
01:14:56.160 --> 01:14:57.957
Paul D?

663
01:15:21.440 --> 01:15:23.271
You shaved.

664
01:15:25.280 --> 01:15:28.556
Yeah. Look bad?

665
01:15:30.040 --> 01:15:31.837
Lookin' good.

666
01:15:34.720 --> 01:15:36.551
Devil's confusion.

667
01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:58.312
- I seen Denver. She tell ya?

668
01:15:59.400 --> 01:16:02.198
You gotta get up
from here. girl.

669
01:16:05.880 --> 01:16:11.000
Look. Denver be here in the day.
I'll be here at night.

670
01:16:11.080 --> 01:16:13.719
I'm gonna take care
of you. ya hear?

671
01:16:13.800 --> 01:16:16.030
Startin' now.

672
01:16:24.560 --> 01:16:27.950
What. baby? What?

673
01:16:32.440 --> 01:16:36.228
She leave me.

674
01:16:38.640 --> 01:16:40.437
She gone again.

675
01:16:40.560 --> 01:16:43.074
Oh. girl. Don't cry.

676
01:16:44.320 --> 01:16:46.709
She leave me.

677
01:16:46.840 --> 01:16:49.274
Sethe. Sethe.

678
01:16:50.520 --> 01:16:52.750
Paul...

679
01:16:52.840 --> 01:16:56.389
she my best thing.

680
01:16:58.920 --> 01:17:01.798
You your best thing. Sethe.

681
01:17:05.240 --> 01:17:07.231
You are.

682
01:17:11.240 --> 01:17:13.071
Me?

683
01:17:15.840 --> 01:17:18.149
Me?

684
01:17:25.600 --> 01:17:30.196
And the beat.
beat of your heart.

685
01:17:33.880 --> 01:17:36.917
- Love it...

686
01:17:37.040 --> 01:17:39.156
more than the lungs...

687
01:17:39.280 --> 01:17:42.556
that need yet...

688
01:17:42.680 --> 01:17:45.433
to breathe free air;

689
01:17:46.680 --> 01:17:49.069
more than the womb...

690
01:17:49.200 --> 01:17:51.760
that holds life;

691
01:17:53.280 --> 01:17:56.829
more than the private parts...
that give life.

692
01:17:56.960 --> 01:18:00.953
- That's right.
- Love your heart.

693
01:18:01.080 --> 01:18:04.038
- Yes! Love your heart!

694
01:18:04.160 --> 01:18:06.958
This... this...

695
01:18:08.040 --> 01:18:10.156
this is the prize.

696
01:18:12.320 --> 01:18:14.117
- Amen.
- Yes!

697
01:18:14.240 --> 01:18:17.710
- Amen.
- This is the prize.

698
01:18:21.600 --> 01:18:23.397
Amen.

699
01:18:28.160 --> 01:18:31.516
- Thank you. sister.
- Thank you. sister.

700
01:18:37.880 --> 01:18:40.235
I feel it.

701
01:18:47.560 --> 01:18:49.710
Bless you. Bless you.

702
01:18:49.840 --> 01:18:51.876
- Bless you.
- Hallelujah!

703
01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:54.719
Hallelujah!
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

704
01:18:58.600 --> 01:19:01.398
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

705
01:19:02.305 --> 01:20:02.751
